headline.main: POLITICAL AND MISCELLANEOUS ITEMS.; Parisian Sentiment about the Soule Duels.

docs.lead_paragraph: EMILE DE GIRARDIN returns to the Presse after a long absence, in an article upon DROUYN DE L'HUYS' circular, announcing that the fleets were ordered to enter the Black Sea. This article has attracted much notice.

docs.lead_paragraph: DEATH OF MISSIONARIES.--Three female Missionaries of the American Baptist Missionary Union have recently deceased--Mrs. Rose, of the mission in Arracan, British Burmah, and Mrs. Shermer and Mrs Crocker, of the mission to the Bassas, West Africa--all within a year of their residence.

headline.main: WILLIAMSBURG CITY.; THE PRESS. Sketch of a Diacourse of Rev. Thomas K. Beecher, delivered at the New-England Church, Williamsburg.

docs.lead_paragraph: Mr. BEECHER said that the motto, not the text, to his discourse was to be found in the last sentence of the fourth verse of the twelfth chapter of the Prophesy of Daniel--which reads "Many shall run to and fro, and knowledge shall be increased."

headline.main: NEW-YORK CITY.; THE CENTRAL PARK. Adjourned Meeting of the Committee on Lands and Places. ACCIDENT ON THE HUDSON RIVER RAILROAD IMPORTANT ARREST OF FORGERS. THE WELSH FESTIVAL. THE MANDAMUS CASE. THE OMNIBUS PICK-POCKET CASE.-- EX-ALDERMAN STURTEVANT. FATAL RAILROAD ACCIDENT. EXAMINATIONS. MAN BLED TO DEATH. FIRES. AMUSEMENTS THIS EVENING.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Committee of the Board of Councilmen, on Lands and Places, to whom was referred that portion of the Mayor's Message, and other papers relating to the Central Park, held an adjourned meeting at 4 P. M., yesterday--Councilman MATTHEW in the Chair. There was a full attendance of persons interested.
